This paper deals with game theory and decision making under uncertainty, which are core topics in computer science. The use of distance-based modifications to the agent model is a novel approach that is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the various instantiations of the model, which involves optimization and regret minimization, making it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the connections between the proposed solution concept and existing ones, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
